steve blackham wrote:
> I wonder how a 1.8 CIS in line four (or the 2.0 block with a cis head)
> would power the green bus.  It's probably a 1000 pound lighter than a
> vanagon (according to door post stickers a mk 2 jetta is 200 lbs
> heavier than a transporter).  You wouldn't have to rotate the engine.
> The engine compartment is taller.  Have to check if the 1.8 would bolt
> to a 091 tranny.  

You would need an adapter plate which is about $500 from Kennedy 
Engineering.  Otherwise, no major problems fitting the engine to a 
baywindow with 091 or 002 tranny.

The radiator out of the Dasher ought to fit both the
> 1.8 and the nose of the bus.  AC would be an option also.  

I'm not sure how the Dasher radiator would fit the nose of the bus. 
Maybe if you had one of those Brazilian-style grilles (but personally I 
think they are fugly).

